                    </div>
                    <span>I head up a team of transcribers and proofreaders; we produce the online and printed versions of our pastor's teachings.  One of my proofreaders gave this to me as a gift, and from the moment I saw the title - and every time I read any of it - I laugh.  It conveys much of what the dry manuals attempt to, but they usually fail to relay the rules in a fashion that is to be remembered and later applied.  Lynne's book paints useful pictures, but what the reader gleans from it is up to them.
<br />I'm giving copies as gifts to my other team members!</span>
                  
              
